The '''470 Express Pierrefonds''' is a express bus route in [[Montreal]], [[Quebec]], [[Canada]]. It is operated by the [[SociÃ©tÃ© de transport de MontrÃ©al]] (STM). The route operates 7 days a week between the hours of 5 AM and 1:30 AM and is a wheelchair accessible route. It serves the [[Boroughs of Montreal|boroughs]] of [[Pierrefonds-Roxboro]] and [[Dollard-des-Ormeaux, Quebec|Dollard-des-Ormeaux]]. It has 23 stops in the eastbound direction and 18 stops in the westbound direction. It is also linked to [[CÃ´te-Vertu (Montreal Metro)|CÃ´te-Vertu Station]] of the [[Montreal Metro]]'s orange line. It serves an average of 9,954 daily passengers during the week day weekday.<ref>http://www.stm.info/en-bref/ra2009.pdf</ref> The fare is $3.00 cash (coins only) or an STM transit pass.
==Schedule== This route started out in 2005 as a rush hour service only but has since become a very popular route with passengers living in the Pierrefonds-Roxboro. Due to the popularity of the route it is now part of the STM's ''10 Minutes Max'' network, which means the routes is served by a bus at maxim intervals of 10 minutes or less between the hours of 6 AM and 9 PM during the week days, however during rush hour intervals are 8 minutes. On the week-end schedules are at intervals of 20 during the day and 30 minutes during the morning and late evening.
